title: S. Jersey Girls: S.J. girls: Pleasantville upends Haddon Heights in tennis playoffs
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports South Jersey Group 2 First Round. Destiny Eden won, 6-4, 7-5, at third singles, and visiting No. 10 Pemberton upended No. 7 Glassboro, 3-2.
South Jersey Group 4 First Round. Alexis Cao and Gabrielle Shvartsman (first doubles) and Meaghan Corej and Serena Lam (second doubles) both shut out their opponents in No. 2 Lenape's 5-0 win over visiting No. 15 Williamstown. 
Central Jersey Group 3 First Round. Rachel Taylor and Anusha Keshireddy won, 6-4, 7-5, at first doubles, and No. 4 Northern Burlington held off No. 13 Wall, 3-2, at home. Soccer North Carolina State recruit Tziarra King (three goals, one assist) had a hand in every goal for Winslow Township in its 4-1 victory at Triton in the Tri-County Conference.
Elsewhere in the Tri-County: 
Lauren Wood put up three goals and one assist to carry host Williamstown past GCIT, 5-1. Williamstown is ranked No. 9 in South Jersey by The Inquirer. 
Ashley Rey delivered a four-save shutout in Glassboro's 2-0 win at Schalick. Lauren Lightcap and Lyndsey Vito scored. 
Burlington County. Alex Kane scored in the first half and No. 10 Cinnaminson held off visiting Rancocas Valley, 1-0. Miranda Sackner had the assist. Marisa DiLeo made 13 saves. Rancocas Valley's Grace Walter had 10 saves. 
Madeline Beascript and Erica Wallace both scored twice in No. 6 Holy Cross' 7-1 home win over New Egypt. Morgan Morocco had a goal and two assists. 
Morgan Papp finished with three goals to lead host Bordentown past Pennsauken, 9-2. 
Kaley Soto and Millisa Yensel scored two goals each as Pemberton dispatched Maple Shade, 4-0, on the road. Kailey Williams made 10 saves. 
Jenna Dobbins scored both goals in Medford Tech's 2-0 victory over visiting Willingboro. 
Olympic. Amirah Ali scored twice to lead No. 2 Eastern to a 4-1 win at Paul VI. Field Hockey Maddie Bickel knocked in three goals as Haddonfield remained undefeated with a 7-0 win at Sterling in the Colonial Conference.
Meghan Smart added two goals and Caroline Bickel added two assists for the Bulldawgs, who improved to 9-0-1. 
In other Colonial Conference action: 
Shannon Super scored in the first half and host Collingswood held on to win, 1-0, against Audubon. 
Jade Freeberg finished with three goals and one assist in West Deptford's 7-1 victory over visiting Overbrook. 
Shannon Agnew recorded a hat trick as Haddon Township cruised to a 9-0 win at Woodbury. Regan Dougherty and Julia Haigh added two goals each. 
Tri-County. Haylee Courant, Moran Emily, and Riley Iaconelli all recorded two goals to lead Gloucester past Pennsville, 9-0, at home. 
Allie Trimble scored twice as host Williamstown won, 4-1, over GCIT. 
Pitman's Olivia Amwake scored in the second half to secure a 1-1 tie over visiting Clayton. Francesca Shipe scored in the first half for Clayton. 
Megan Dyson scored twice in the second half as GCIT rallied to tie Salem, 3-3, on the road. Kaleigh Frampton also scored for GCIT. Autumn Glaspay, Mikera Thomas, and Mikia Thomas scored for Salem, which led by 2-0 at halftime.
